# PROJECT OVERVIEW: Digital Minimalist Project

## Vision
Empower users to achieve digital wellness through mindful technology usage, reducing digital overload while maintaining productivity and meaningful connections.

## Core Features
- **Digital Habit Tracking**: Monitor and analyze screen time, app usage patterns
- **Mindful Notifications**: Smart notification management with focus modes
- **Content Curation**: AI-powered content filtering for meaningful engagement
- **Productivity Tools**: Time-blocking, distraction-free work environments
- **Progress Analytics**: Personal insights and digital wellness metrics

## Target Audience
- Primary users: Digital professionals seeking work-life balance (25-45 years)
- Secondary users: Students and content creators looking to optimize focus time

## Project Goals
- Reduce average daily screen time by 30% for active users
- Increase user-reported productivity and well-being scores
- Build a community of 10,000+ digital minimalists within first year
- Achieve 70%+ user retention rate after 30 days

## Success Metrics
- Daily Active Users (DAU) and Monthly Active Users (MAU)
- Average session duration and feature engagement rates
- User satisfaction scores (NPS > 50)
- Reduction in reported digital stress levels

## Project Philosophy
- Privacy-first: User data stays secure and private
- Non-addictive design: No dark patterns or engagement manipulation
- Evidence-based: Features grounded in behavioral psychology research
- Accessible: Inclusive design for all users
- Senior engineering practices and comprehensive documentation

